Title: Privilege Escalation: Low Privilege User Can View Super Admin-Restricted Employer Data
Description: A low privilege user is able to access sensitive employer data that is strictly meant for Super Admins. Due to a flaw in the access control mechanism, the user can bypass security restrictions and view all employer data, which should only be accessible to Super Admins. This results in a significant confidentiality breach, exposing critical information to unauthorized users.

Impact:

Exposure of sensitive employer data to lower privilege users.
Privacy violations and potential misuse of sensitive business or personal information.
Loss of data confidentiality and trust in the system's access control.
Recommendation:

Strengthen access control mechanisms to ensure Super Admin-restricted data is not accessible by lower privilege users.
Implement and test role-based access control (RBAC) to enforce correct data access boundaries.
Perform security audits to ensure no further privilege escalation vulnerabilities exist.
